    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Buy Predators To Eat the Aphids</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By PATRICIA JONAS</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Jonas, Patricia</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>This Week's gardening suggestion, on controlling aphids (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Aphids are beginning to make their appearance on rose buds and the tender new growth of many plants. They are most efficiently controlled by predators like lady beetles, lacewings and syrphid flies, which can be purchased for release in the garden. They will stay as long as there are aphids to eat. If the beneficial insects can't keep up, a direct spray of horticultural oil will kill aphids and has little residual impact on predators.</p>
        <p>PATRICIA JONAS</p>
      </block>
